			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm reposting this. I'm not sure if it works, the last time I heard, the fear pathing had been changed, not sure if it was fixed.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Maghriste’s Guide to Twilight Sea Dock People.</span>
<br />

<br />
For levels 51-55. 
<br />

<br />
Terrain.
<br />

<br />
Dock A
<br />

<br />
Dock A is at -389.92, -1073.89, -5.66. There are 3 mobs on it:
<br />
Trevor Nalinson – Half Elf Male
<br />
Brodlan Remdo – Human Male
<br />
Liteema Agner – Halfling Female
<br />

<br />
Dock B
<br />

<br />
Dock B is at +150.63, -984.54, +20.60. There are 3 mobs on it:
<br />
Ellen Daleson – Human Female
<br />
Edgar Lemoof – Wood Elf Male
<br />
Rilla Quickeyes – Wood Elf Female
<br />

<br />
Dock C (Katta Dock)
<br />

<br />
Dock C is at -431. 95, -1731.28, -2436. There are 2 mobs on it:
<br />
Herald Shelia Gransith – Human Female
<br />
Brolan Geppal – Half Elf Male
<br />

<br />
Katta Entrance
<br />

<br />
The Entrance to Katta Castellum is at -107.54, -1879.02, +94.69. There are 2 guards here:
<br />
Legionnaire Eandalion – Human Male Guard
<br />
Legionnaire Frankulus – Human Male Guard
<br />

<br />
From Dock C, you follow the ramp up to the entrance to Katta Castellum.
<br />

<br />
Setup.
<br />

<br />
Spell Lineup:
<br />
1) Drain Soul (Deflux at 54)
<br />
2) Dooming Darkness
<br />
3) Invoke Fear
<br />
4) Splurt
<br />
5) Lich/Summon Companion
<br />
6) Bond of Death
<br />
7) Augment Death/Paralyzing Earth
<br />
8.) Feign Death
<br />

<br />
Stand at -535.67, -1151.02, -11.87. Cast pet and have it guard. Invoke Death from 51-53, Minion of Shadows from 53-55. Cast Augment Death on your pet, you will want this on all the time. From this location, the Dock C is east. Docks A and B, as they will be reffered to, are North. You can see Dock A, it will be right next to you, a safe distance away. Keep Dead Man Floating and Arch Shielding up at all times.
<br />

<br />
Breaking the Spawn.
<br />

<br />
Cast Lich, run across to Dock C, and cast Splurt on Herald Shelia Gransith. Wait till she’s in the water, and run back to your pet. Start spamming Dooming Darkness till she gets in range and it lets you cast. This will give you just enough time to have her snared by the time she is on land and halfway to your pet. Sick the pet on her, step back a little bit, and cast Invoke Fear. Now, there is a timing issue here that you’ll have to work with to get it down to a science. It’s easy enough to figure out with a little practice. 
<br />

<br />
Once Shelia is dead, target Trevor Nalinson on Dock A and cast Darkness and then Bond of Death, sick pet and Invoke Fear. Once Trevor is dead, run back to Dock C and pull Brolan Geppal repeating the above mentioned process with Shelia on Brolan. Once Brolan is dead, pull Brodlan Remdo, and then Liteema Agner with the same method you used with Trevor. You will alternate Splurt and Bond of Death on the mobs, Splurt one mob, BoD the next. This will make sure that you keep up your hitpoints as you will have Lich on all the time. 
<br />

<br />
Now that Docks A and C are clear, tell your pet to follow you and run to -14.59, -1027.73, +42.86. Park the pet here and pull Ellen Daleson from Dock B with Dooming Darkness. Fall back to -128.95, -1079.68, -0.67. Cast Bond of Death, sick pet, and Invoke Fear. Continue alternating Splurt and BoD here, pulling Edgar Lemoof next, and then Rilla Quickeyes.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=359958" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: red">Sage Maghriste Necroforo</span> </a>
<br />
Arch Lich of Veeshan
<br />
<img src="http://www.megadeth.com/releases/discography/images/albums/full/cte.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
