			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Now that Dock B is clear, keep pet parked, and run to the Katta Entrance. When you reach -183.77, -1779.16, +44.16, you will be at the bottom of the 3rd ramp down from the Katta Entrance. Cast Summon Companion and tell him to guard immediately or he will run back to the hill by Dock B. Be careful if you have him follow instead of guard because if he walks over the edge of the ramps to Katta he will poof. Now that the pet is guarded, face east towards the wall. You will see the ramp goes up, on either side of the ramp are ledges that frame the ramp. Stand on the right ledge and walk slowly up the ramp until you see Legionnaire Eandalion aggro. Then step back to the pet. This is how you can pull the guards single. This does not always work, but it works a lot of the time. If you get them together, simply Fear one and then Dark/Fear/Splurt or Bod, the other and let your pet kill it. You could also Root one but it can be a pain. When Fear wears off the guard will come running back to you, so it’s no big deal. Once Eandalion is down, assuming you got him single, just sick your pet on Frankulus and Dark/Fear/DoT him. 
<br />

<br />
Once all 10 mobs are dead, click Lich off and run back to -535.67, -1151.02, -11.87. You will have a few minutes to rest up for the next round, maybe 3-5 minutes. Once Herald Shelia Gransith repops, start all over again. This is good XP all the way to 55, it slows down a bit at 54, but you’ll feel better if you just grind out 54. Once you’re 55, you can move on to Katta Guards (Outside Graveyard).
<br />

<br />
I’ve been meaning to write this for awhile now and have just been putting it off, hope it helps out. 
<br />

<br />
Notice: As always this guide is based on assumptions. 1) That you have Journeyman’s Boots, Traveler’s Boots, or Run Speed 3. 2) That you have all the spells mentioned. 3) That you are not a level 51 newbie. (Don’t ya just love EBay???) 
<br />

<br />
Notes:
<br />

<br />
All of this is up debate due to personal style. My way is an exact science that works fast, efficient and every time. You will not get adds at 51 except for when pulling the guards unless you screw up and let your pet and the mob it’s killing get to close to another mob. This only happened to me once. 
<br />

<br />
If something happens, it’s taking too long to kill a mob, or a mob actually gets physical with you and you lose more health than normal, just Drain Soul/Deflux to give yourself a boost.
<br />

<br />
The only loot is a very rare Fishing Pole which is the same one that you can buy at most Fishing Vendors across EverQuest.
<br />

<br />
At level 55 all of the Mobs will be Light Blue, they will all be Dark Blue before this level.
<br />

<br />
This is also decent AAXP even at 55 when everything is Light Blue. AAXP sucks pre-60, so when I say decent, I mean decent AAXP for levels 51-55.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=359958" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: red">Sage Maghriste Necroforo</span> </a>
<br />
Arch Lich of Veeshan
